Pumpkin Spice Choco Chip
Soft pumpkin cookies with warm spices and dark chocolate
classic
Spiced, Chocolate, Soft

INGREDIENTS:
2 1/2 cups gluten-free all-purpose flour
1 tsp baking soda
1/4 tsp salt
1 tsp pumpkin pie spice
6 tbsp butter
4 1/2 tbsp pumpkin puree
3/4 cup granulated sugar
3/4 cup packed brown sugar
2 eggs
3/4 tsp vanilla
1 cup dark chocolate chips

INSTRUCTIONS:
Preheat oven to 350Â°F. Line baking sheets with parchment paper
Beat butter, pumpkin puree, and sugars until smooth and well combined
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until well blended
Add flour, baking soda, salt, and pumpkin pie spice. Beat until just combined
Stir in dark chocolate chips
Drop tablespoonsful of dough about 2 inches apart onto prepared sheets
Bake until cookies lose their shiny appearance, about 12-15 minutes
Cool on baking sheet for 1 minute before removing. Makes 48 cookies